gomodel:SYNGO_1370  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The figure show that Drosophila 4E-BP regulates synaptic properties of the NMJ; precisely, knockdown of 4eBP (Thor) in motor neuron reduced the presynaptic release of neurotransmitter.\n\n2/10/2017 Pim\n- Fig.2 shows the involvement of a Insulin->Tor pathway that regulates SV release. In subsequence figures the authors shows that this is via a nuclear mechanism that reslts in translational regulation of Complexin. Moreover, the 4E-BP protein is a known translational regulator. Together this shows that the effect of tor on SV release is indirectly via regulation of translation.. Experimental description: w1118 as wild-type strain" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1370" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_7227" .

